As I pack up my studio, it is a good time reflect on the progress I've made. A year ago the only tools I had were a good set of pliers, a drill, and a dremel. I've invested everything I have back in. Now I'm upgrading to a larger studio, and in a couple days I'm releasing a fabrication that I'm very proud of. If it weren't for the love I have for this journey, and the love others have shown me, none of this would be possible. HUGE thank you to my family, friends, fellow artists, and complete strangers for the kind words and support🙏 
and a special thank you to my lovely lady @liz_ard_breath for putting up with my workaholic tendencies, and supporting this dream❤

{[Universally Unfurling]} •Hand-Fabricated .925 Sterling Silver
•50 x Multicolored Sapphire /Available/

Featuring a body of solid .925 sterling silver and a total of 50 multicolored sapphires (thanks to @candyman_crystals), this pendant is truly one of a kind. The silver unfurls from itself in an infinitely reproducing loop at the heart of this pendant. Extending out from the center is a series of symmetrical geometry and filigree carefully hand carved and replicating the growth of an unfurling fern. Sapphires coat the interior of this pendant bringing it to life as flashes of light dance across its surface in the sunlight. With a balanced orchestration of pink, orange, yellow, and purple sapphires this pendant is eye catching. Live on my Etsy now or through DM. Link in my bio. Much love ♥️♥️♥️

🔮As i continue with this recap of my older thesis works, we get closer to understanding how i came to my current conclusions. 📰The title for this color pencil drawing says it all in my opinion.
"A Wrinkle In Time and Face" 🤓
After finishing what was, at the time, 2 exhausting feats in this vein, it only felt right to push it even further. I can be massicistically ambitious sometimes 😭
🏞So instead of letting the process grow on its own with a constant focus on pursuing interesting folds and gradient fluxes, i took more control here and manipulated the same exact shirt into more fitting forms for a grand slam "high"class portrait!! 😯
🥑No lines or gradients were made up for any of these. i sculpted the shirt and drew directly from life with a photo of myself wearing my signature hat at the time on the side.
🥋 In the end i managed to flex the collars into intentional areas of hair or lashes or eye veins ✊🤠, and i played with the level of wrinkle and bulbousness of folds to push lighter or darker areas. 🌬☁My theoretical effort here was to explore how far i could take the concepts of paradolia, or cloud watching in a way. I could already see so many engaging visuals from prior abstract works, but here the face tends to distract from nature's ability to be ambigious in this decontextualized field. 🌈Although when i managed to see apart from the facial recognition, a whole new world of thinking grew in my mind. This sensual, and specifically textural, realm is soooo undeniably deep, layered, and flexible. I was so inspired to acknowledge what the gaze in this drawing was glazing over for.
🥛A blank space is a sacred place 🙏
Black Color Pencil on Paper, 2013 💪
